```julia
function clean_column(col)
    return Symbol(strip(lowercase(String(col)), '\n', '\t'), '_')
end
```

This function takes a `Symbol` as input (which represents a column name in Julia's DataFrames) and returns a new `Symbol` with the specified cleaning applied. It uses `strip` to remove leading and trailing whitespaces, `lowercase` to make the string lowercase, and then replaces spaces and hyphens with an underscore using `String` conversion and symbol creation. The `'\n'` and `'\t'` are specifically mentioned to strip newline and tab characters, which can also be considered whitespace in some contexts.
